    br
      .row
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-globe.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title Turn any SQL query into a JSON endpoint
            p 
              | Define your SQL database connections and queries, and they'll be made available behind a URL in JSON format. Also works with
              |  HTTP, Redis, Google Sheets, Redshift, BigQuery and so on.
              
        /! /.mini-feature
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-eye.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title Watch any JSON endpoint and be notified of changes
            p Get sub-second updates on changes to any JSON endpoint anywhere. Subscribe to every refresh or just the ones with changes
        /! /.mini-feature
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-refresh.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title Refresh datagrams per a schedule
            p Data changes at different speeds. Take control of when datagrams get refreshed so users always have relevant information without overloading your datastores
        /! /.mini-feature
      /! /.row
    h4.content-title
      span How does it help me?
    br

      .row
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-share.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title Share data from anywhere...
            p Give your team access to reports from SQL databases, Elasticsearch, MongoDB, Redis, Redshift, Google Drive and so on...
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-ticket.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title ... with complete control!
            p
              | ... without providing access credentials. Generate and expire tokens 
              | to control who can access which queries.
        .mini-feature
          i.fa.fa-globe.mini-feature-icon.text-secondary
          .mini-feature-text
            h5.mini-feature-title Free your data team
            p Let your data team concentrate on confirming hypothesis. Let datagram do the refreshing of reports and notifying interested parties.

        /! /.mini-feature


